12 SECTION 26. AMENDMENT. Section 65-06-01 of the North Dakota Century Code is
13 amended and reenacted as follows:
14 65-06-01. Volunteer firefighter, emergency or disaster volunteer, community
15 emergency response team member, in training defined.
16 The term "volunteer firefighter" means any active member of an organized volunteer fire
17 department of this state and any other individual performing services as a volunteer firefighter
18 for a municipality at the request of the chief or other individual in command of the fire
19 department of that municipality or of any other officer of that municipality having authority to
20 demand service as a firefighter. Firefighters who are paid a regular wage or stipend by the
21 municipality for serving as a firefighter, or whose entire time is devoted to service as a firefighter
22 for the municipality, for the purpose of this chapter, are not volunteer firefighters.
23 The term "emergency or disaster volunteer" means any individual serving without
24 remuneration who is actively engaged in training to qualify as a disaster emergency worker or is
25 responding to a hazard, emergency disaster, or enemy attack on this country, and who is
26 registered with the disaster emergency organization of a municipality, which has been officially
27 recognized by the director of the state division of homeland security and emergency
28 management.
29 The term "in training" means only those periods of time, during which an emergency or
30 disaster volunteer is receiving instruction, or is engaged in exercises or operations, in
